Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deletePinGuide(25.10)                                    deletePinGuide(25.10)

Name
       deletePinGuide - Deletes a pin guide object in the floorplan

Syntax
       deletePinGuide

       [-help]

       {  -pin  <pin_name>  |  -pinGroup  <pin_group_name> | -net <net_name> |
       -netGroup <net_group_name> | -name <object_name> | -all }

       [-cell <ptn_name> | -net <net_name> | -netGroup <net_group_name>]

       Deletes a pin guide object in the floorplan. You can use  this  command
       during partition floorplanning.

Parameters
       -all   Specifies that all pin guides will be deleted.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -cell <ptn_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the module. The module name is not re-
              quired if the command is run on a top-level module.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each deletePinGuide parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deletePinGuide

       -name <object_name>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the partition pin guide object. If you
              specify this parameter, the command  will  automatically  detect
              whether  the object is a pin, pin group, net, net group, or bus.
              In case there are different objects with the same name, the com-
              mand selects the object with the following precedence:

              * If a cell name is specified, the command  selects  the  object
                with the following precedence:

                * pin

                * pin group

                * net

                * net group or bus

              * If  a  cell name is not specified, the command selects the ob-
                ject with the following precedence:

                * net

                * net group or bus

              For example, if the value of <objectName> is P1, and there is  a
              pin  group  named P1 as well as a bus named P1, the command will
              select the pin group named P1.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -net <net_name>
              For nets, specifies the name of the net.  For  buses,  specifies
              the name of the bus or the bus radix.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -netGroup <net_group_name>
              Specifies the name of the net group.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -pin <pin_name>
              Specifies the name of the pin.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -pinGroup <pin_group_name>
              Specifies the name of the pin group.

              Default: By default the name is defRGuideName.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command deletes a pin guide object named group_1:

       deletePinGuide -name group_1

